name: spawning_ground
description: Example form for spawning ground surveys

page_level.name: spawning_ground_p
page_level.label: Spawning Ground Surveys

elements.name: start_not_listed
elements.label: Start point not listed
elements.validation_message: "The start point river mile value must be greater than -1 and less than 1000"
elements.dynamic_label: "Please enter river mile value of the start point"

elements.name: end_not_listed
elements.label: End point not listed
elements.validation_message: "The end point river mile value must be greater than -1 and less than 1000"
elements.dynamic_label: "Please enter river mile value of the end point"

elements.name: start_temperature_c
elements.label: Water temperature (degrees C)
elements.validation_message: "The start point water temperature must be between 0 and 38 degrees Celsius"

elements.name: target_species_label
elements.label: For Target species, please select all species you intended to survey, whether you saw them or not. This allows automatically entering zeros for species you intended to survey but did not see.

elements.name: fish_redd_zeros
elements.label: For target species you did not see, should zeros be auto-entered for fish, redds, or both?

elements.name: observations_yes_no
elements.label: Did you see any fish or fish redds?

elements.name: survey_complete_yes_no
elements.label: Are you at the end of this survey?

elements.name: end_temperature_c
elements.label: End point water temperature (C)
elements.validation_message: "The end point water temperature must be between 0 and 38 degrees Celsius"
elements.dynamic_label: "Water temperature in degrees C at end of the survey (optional)"

elements.name: my_element_38
elements.label: Anything other than a "Completed survey" requires explanation below

elements.name: survey_comment
elements.label: Survey comments (optional)
elements.validation_message: "Please explain why survey was not completed"

elements.name: survey_type
elements.label: Survey type
elements.dynamic_label: "Please enter the survey type for " + species_text

elements.name: explan_survey_types
elements.label:
Index:  Index area surveyed on a regular basis

Supplemental:  Supplemental survey not counted regularly, or for areas outside of the index area

Spot: Spot check

Exploratory: Exploratory survey, usually performed to find the uppermost extent of spawning

elements.name: redd_coordinates
elements.label: Redd coordinates
elements.description: Allows entering coordinates post survey, as well as providing a simpler display for output.

elements.name: redd_fish_yes_no
elements.label: Redd fish?
elements.dynamic_label: "Any live " + species_text +  " associated with the redd?"

elements.name: show_fish
elements.label: Show fish fields
elements.dynamic_value: if(ZCDisplayValue_observation_type == "Live fish" || ZCDisplayValue_observation_type == "Carcass") {"yes"} else if( ZCDisplayValue_observation_type == "Fish redd" && ZCDisplayValue_redd_fish_yes_no == "Yes") {"yes"} else {"no"}

elements.name: count_label
elements.label: NOTE: You must enter a count value of 1 if you want to record data for individual fish (such as spawn condition, length measurements, or scale samples).

elements.name: fish_location_yes_no
elements.label: Do you want to enter location of the fish?
elements.condition_value: if(ZCDisplayValue_observation_type == "Fish redd") {false} else {species_fish > -1 && show_fish == "yes" && entry_method_text == "realtime" && Number(fish_count) > 0}
elements.dynamic_label: "Do you want to enter the location of the " + species_text + "?"

elements.name: fish_coordinates
elements.label: Fish coordinates
elements.description: Allows entering coordinates post survey, as well as providing a simpler display for output.

elements.name: cwt_detected
elements.label: CWT detected?
elements.dynamic_label: "Did you detect a CWT in the " + species_text + "?"

elements.name: sample_number_uuid
elements.label: Unique sample number (UUID)
elements.dynamic_value: if(fish_sample_text == "None" || fish_sample_text == "Scale") {""} else if(sample_number.length > 0) {sample_number + "_" + generateUUID()} else {generateUUID()}

elements.name: scale_card_position_number
elements.label: Scale card position number
elements.validation_message: "Scale card position number must be between 1 and 20"
